criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with fibromyalgia diagnosed according to criteria formulated by American
             College Rheumatology 2002;

          -  Patients whose scores for pain intensity is more than 30mm;

          -  Patients who are 20 to 60 years old;

          -  Patients who fully understand the process of this research and who are willing to
             provide informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  The widespread muscular-skeletal pain is caused by some kind of disease, surgery, or
             other external interference factors (except fibromyalgia);

          -  Patients with mental disorders, or other serious organic diseases, such as organ
             failure;

          -  Patients who take oral anodyne medications or accept other interventions for pain
             relief during the treatment;

          -  Pregnant or lactating women;

          -  Patients currently participating in another clinical trial.
